                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.24/197: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-28T12:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1923—12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>101. Acting general manager International Railways informs me that his New York
                    office has authorized him to sell Mexican Government <pb facs="0693" n="569"
                        xml:id="pg_569"/> 1,000 barrels of oil per week at Ayutla if there is no
                    objection made by the Government of Guatemala or the American Minister. Please
                    instruct me by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geissler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
